  - summation: [{'dbId': 2894860, 'displayName': 'Mutations in the heterodimerization domain (HD) and PEST dom...', 'text': 'Mutations in the heterodimerization domain (HD) and PEST domain of NOTCH1 are frequently found in cis in T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia. While HD mutations alone result in up to ~10-fold increase in NOTCH1 transcriptional activity and PEST domain mutations alone result in up to ~2-fold increase in NOTCH1 transcriptional activity, in cis mutations of HD and PEST domains act synergistically, increasing NOTCH1 transcriptional activity up to ~40-fold (Weng et al. 2004).', 'className': 'Summation', 'schemaClass': 'Summation'}]
